  <title>WebKit2.WebContext.prototype.set_favicon_database_directory</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function set_favicon_database_directory(path: String): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for webkit_web_context_set_favicon_database_directory()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Set the directory path to be used to store the favicons database
for <code>context</code> on disk. Passing <code>null</code> as <code>path</code> means using the
default directory for the platform (see g_get_user_data_dir()).</p>  <p>Calling this method also means enabling the favicons database for
its use from the applications, so that's why it's expected to be
called only once. Further calls for the same instance of
<link xref="WebKit2.WebContext"/> won't cause any effect.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>path</code></title>
  <p>an absolute path to the icon database
directory or <code>null</code> to use the defaults</p>
</item>
</terms>

